<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,356,776]" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,407,535,560]" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
The so far only known real 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[732,832,537,560]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,832,537,560]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">Evonima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the Afrotropics is 
<taxonomicName authority="Hacker, 2012" authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westafricana">
<emphasis box="[1164,1341,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">E. westafricana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." pageId="20" pageNumber="245" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref13560" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">Hacker, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, displaying very similar genitalia structure to that of the 
<typeStatus box="[857,905,573,597]" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus (
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1865" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aperta">
<emphasis box="[1160,1341,573,596]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">Evonima aperta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." pageId="20" pageNumber="245" pagination="505" refId="ref14588" refString="Walker, F. (1865) List of the Specimens of Lepidopterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum. Part XXXII, Supplement 2, 505." type="journal article" year="1865">Walker, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) and its Asiatic relatives. The other two species treated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[859,959,609,632]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[859,959,609,632]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">Evonima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(van Son, 1933)" authorityName="van Son" authorityYear="1933" baseAuthorityName="van Son" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[972,1283,607,632]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Poecilonola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis box="[972,1099,607,632]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">E. littoralis</emphasis>
(van 
<bibRefCitation author="Son" box="[1161,1275,608,632]" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" pagination="181 - 232" refId="ref14378" refString="Son, van G. (1933) A revision of the South African moths of the tribe Nolini. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 15 (2), 181 - 232." type="journal article" year="1933">Son, 1933</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hacker, 2012" authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruhija">
<emphasis box="[1337,1435,607,632]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">E. ruhija</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." box="[151,301,644,669]" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref13560" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">Hacker, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
differ significantly in male genitalia from the ground plan of Asiatic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[1076,1176,645,668]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1076,1176,645,668]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">Evonima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[1230,1406,644,668]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westafricana">
<emphasis box="[1230,1406,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">E. westafricana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it is shown in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." box="[317,545,679,704]" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref13560" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">
Hacker 
<emphasis box="[407,458,679,704]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">et al</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, suggesting a need for erecting a distinct genus for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="van Son" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[1143,1240,679,704]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Poecilonola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis box="[1143,1240,679,704]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="245">littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[1298,1366,679,704]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruhija">
